Partial review.

I'd really expect that when this is moved to the new library, the request/response queue will be removed and greatly simplified down to something like:


boost::asio::ip::tcp::socket sock(...);
std::array<uint8_t, 256> buf;
sock.async_read_some(boost::asio::buffer(buf), [](){
   modbusParseRequestTCP(status, buf.data(), buf.size();
});

if that's not possible, and we end up going the multi-threaded approach, please document why in the commit message.
